{
  "version": 1,
  "name": "Dual-Power Source OR Circuit",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "Dual-Power Source OR Circuit",
    "description": "One USB tile powers two OR inputs. Press the west tact: full 5 V → Schottky → the shared node → 470Ω → red LED (bright). Press the east tact: a 10kΩ–10kΩ divider off the same USB gives about 2.5 V at the tap — enough to OR through its Schottky but the LED is dim or off (not enough headroom). Press both: the higher rail wins. Compare lesson 35 (both buttons at 5 V) and lesson 17 (divider without diode OR). Schottkys at 90° (cathode toward center); LED at 90°."
  },
